tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement for their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a new sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigned key UI components, and applied consistent styling across all
  sections to create a more calming and professional user experience.
overview: The user wanted to transform their sleep questionnaire app from a
  generic-looking interface to a visually appealing and professional one. I
  began by analyzing the existing design, identifying issues like a bland color
  palette and uninspired form elements. My approach involved introducing a
  calming, sleep-themed color palette, redesigning the main form layout with
  subtle background elements and an improved progress indicator, and enhancing
  the welcome screen with feature cards. I then polished individual form
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders. A key decision was to
  apply consistent card-style groupings to all questionnaire sections, moving
  away from the old gray boxes. The report section also received significant
  visual upgrades. The outcome is an app with a cohesive, calming, and
  professional aesthetic that aligns well with a sleep health application.
